<section xml:id="recursion-summary">
  <title>Recursion Summary</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this unit you learned about <term>recursion</term>. A recursive method
      calls itself (contains a call to the method from inside of the method). A
      recursive method should have at least one way to stop the recursion. This
      is called a base case.
    </p>

    <idx>recursion</idx>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="concept-summary-index-0-6">
    <title>Concept Summary</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            <term>base case</term> - A way to stop the recursive calls. This is
            a return without a recursive call.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            <term>call stack</term> - The call stack keeps track of the methods
            that are called while the code executes. It keeps track of the local
            variables and where the call will return to.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            <term>recursive method</term> - A method that contains at least one
            call to itself inside the method.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="vocabulary-practice-8">
    <title>Vocabulary Practice</title>
    <activity label="ch12rec_match_1">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Drag the item from the left and drop it on its corresponding answer on
          the right. Click the "Check Me" button to see if you are correct.
        </p>
      </statement>

      <feedback>
        <p>Review the summaries above.</p>
      </feedback>

      <cardsort>
        <match>
          <premise order="1">A method that calls itself</premise>
          <response>recursive method</response>
        </match>

        <match>
          <premise order="2">The stack of calls to methods</premise>
          <response>call stack</response>
        </match>

        <match>
          <premise order="3">The case when the method doesn't call itself</premise>
          <response>base case</response>
        </match>
      </cardsort>
    </activity>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="common-mistakes-8">
    <title>Common Mistakes</title>
    <blockquote>
      <p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              Missing the recursive call. Be sure to look for a call to the same
              method.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Getting confused about when a recursive method returns and what it
              returns.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Assuming you understand what the recursion is doing without
              tracing all of it.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </blockquote>
  </subsection>
</section>
